-- China appoints Bank of China as yuan clearing bank in Paris
-- By Kevin Yao and Xiaoyi Shao
-- Mon Sep 15, 2014 04:21AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, Sept 15 (Reuters) - China's central bank said on Monday it had appointed Bank of China <601988.SS>, the country's main foreign exchange lender, as the yuan clearing service bank in Paris - the latest move to expand the offshore yuan market.

The People's Bank of China made the announcement in a statement posted on its website, www.pbc.gov.cn The Bank of China <3988.HK> was previously selected to provide yuan clearing services in Frankfurt and Australia.